goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any correlation between the effectiveness of Penicillin and Streptomycin against different bacteria.

goals.question: What is the relationship between Gram Staining and effectiveness of antibiotics against the bacteria?
goals.visualization: Box plot of Penicillin, Streptomycin and Neomycin columns grouped by Gram Staining
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any difference in the effectiveness of antibiotics against bacteria based on their Gram Staining.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Penicillin'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['Penicillin'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Penicillin'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Penicillin'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Penicillin'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin effectiveness against the bacteria?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = data.plot(kind='scatter', x='Penicillin', y='Streptomycin', c='Gram_Staining', cmap='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Penicillin and Streptomycin effectiveness against the bacteria?', wrap=True)
    chart.axvline(data['Penicillin'].median(), color='red', label='Penicillin Median')
    chart.axhline(data['Streptomycin'].median(), color='green', label='Streptomycin Median')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['Penicillin', 'Streptomycin', 'Neomycin', 'Gram_Staining']]
    data.boxplot(by='Gram_Staining')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Gram Staining and effectiveness of antibiotics against the bacteria?', wrap=True)
    plt.suptitle('')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
